de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.searchAlgorithms.choice.fpComparison
Class FpComparisonChoicePoint

java.lang.Object
  de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.searchAlgorithms.choice.fpComparison.FpComparisonChoicePoint
All Implemented Interfaces:
ChoicePoint
Direct Known Subclasses:
DoubleComparisonChoicePoint, FloatComparisonChoicePoint
public abstract class FpComparisonChoicePoint
extends java.lang.Object
implements ChoicePoint

A FpComparisonChoicePoint is generated whenever one of the instructions dcmpg, dcmpl, fcmpg or fcmpl is reached. The instructions are used to compare floating point types and leaves four possibilities. This choice point will make sure all four will be checked. Due to its abstract nature, concrete choice point can be derived from it.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-03-10
Author:
Tim Majchrzak

                           throws SymbolicExecutionException
Create the floating point comparison choice point.

Parameters:
frame - The currently executed Frame.
pc - The pc of the instruction that generates the ChoicePoint.
pcNext - The pc of the instruction after the lcmp instruction.
less - If set to true, the choice point will have the behaviour of dcmpl / fcmpl; otherwise, it will behave like dcmpg / fcmpg.
leftTerm - The term of double or float variables and constants of the left hand side of the comparison.
rightTerm - The term of double or float variables and constants of the right hand side of the comparison.
Throws:
SymbolicExecutionException - On fatal problems applying the constraint.

applyStateChanges

public void applyStateChanges()
Apply any state changes required for the current choice. This will push the int value -1, 0 or 1 onto the stack and add a corresponding constraint for the long variable.

The method can only be called after changeToNextChoice() has been run. Calling it another time before running changeToNextChoice() will have an exception thrown.

Specified by:
applyStateChanges in interface ChoicePoint
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - If no new value has been prepared yet of if there are no more values to be applied at all.
